data.name: Ruleslabel.Text
data.value: Rules and Instructions: 1. This is a windows form Snake and Ladders game. 2. Two players take turns rolling the dice and the characters move according to the number that appears on the top of the dice. 3. If a player lands on a square with the base of a ladder, then the player climbs up the ladder. 4. If a player lands on a square in which there is a mouth of a snake, then the player slides down the snake. 5. Players take the turn clockwise and the game terminates until one player reaches the final square and is then pronounced the winner. 6. Each player should press their player button before rolling the dice. 7. Player one always starts rolling. 8. Each player is given one default shield to protect them from the snake. 9. If a player lands on 35, he jumps a number of levels according to the dice number. 10. If a player lands on 44, he goes back one step. 11. If a player lands on 94 his turn is skipped and the other player plays twice.
